<h1 id="module-wise-explanation">10. Module-Wise Explanation</h1>
<h2 id="authentication-module">10.1 Authentication Module</h2>
<p>The authentication module handles registration, login, password
verification, token creation, and current-user lookup.</p>
<h3 id="responsibilities">Responsibilities</h3>
<ul>
<li>Hash user passwords.</li>
<li>Validate login credentials.</li>
<li>Generate access tokens.</li>
<li>Identify the current authenticated user.</li>
<li>Enforce role-based access.</li>
</ul>
<h3 id="sample-behavior">Sample Behavior</h3>
<p>If a user enters invalid credentials, the backend returns
<code>401 Unauthorized</code>. If the credentials are valid, the backend
issues a bearer token that the frontend can reuse for API calls.</p>
